    "## 1. Bidirectional RNNs\n",
    "\n",
    "### Concept\n",
    "\n",
    "**Standard RNN:** Processes sequence left-to-right\n",
    "- Only sees past context\n",
    "- $h_t = f(h_{t-1}, x_t)$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Bidirectional RNN:** Processes both directions\n",
    "- Forward pass: left-to-right\n",
    "- Backward pass: right-to-left\n",
    "- Combines both contexts\n",
    "\n",
    "### Mathematical Formulation\n",
    "\n",
    "**Forward hidden state:**\n",
    "$\\overrightarrow{h_t} = f(\\overrightarrow{h_{t-1}}, x_t)$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Backward hidden state:**\n",
    "$\\overleftarrow{h_t} = f(\\overleftarrow{h_{t+1}}, x_t)$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Combined output:**\n",
    "$h_t = [\\overrightarrow{h_t}; \\overleftarrow{h_t}]$ (concatenation)\n",
    "\n",
    "### When to Use\n",
    "\n",
    "✅ **Use Bidirectional:**\n",
    "- Text classification\n",
    "- Named entity recognition\n",
    "- Sentiment analysis\n",
    "- Any task where full sequence is available\n",
    "\n",
    "❌ **Don't Use Bidirectional:**\n",
    "- Real-time prediction\n",
    "- Online learning\n",
    "- When future context unavailable"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def create_bidirectional_model(vocab_size=10000, embedding_dim=128, \n",
    "                               max_length=100, num_classes=2):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Create bidirectional LSTM for text classification\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Args:\n",
    "        vocab_size: Vocabulary size\n",
    "        embedding_dim: Embedding dimension\n",
    "        max_length: Maximum sequence length\n",
    "        num_classes: Number of output classes\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "        Bidirectional LSTM model\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    inputs = keras.Input(shape=(max_length,))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Embedding layer\n",
    "    x = layers.Embedding(vocab_size, embedding_dim)(inputs)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Bidirectional LSTM\n",
    "    # Output dimension = 2 * units (forward + backward)\n",
    "    x = layers.Bidirectional(layers.LSTM(64, return_sequences=True))(x)\n",
    "    x = layers.Bidirectional(layers.LSTM(32))(x)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Dense layers\n",
    "    x = layers.Dense(64, activation='relu')(x)\n",
    "    x = layers.Dropout(0.5)(x)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    outputs = layers.Dense(num_classes, activation='softmax')(x)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    model = Model(inputs, outputs, name='Bidirectional_LSTM')\n",
    "    return model\n",
    "\n",
    "bi_model = create_bidirectional_model()\n",
    "print(\"Bidirectional LSTM model created\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nNote: Bidirectional layer doubles the output dimension\")\n",
    "print(f\"LSTM(64) → Bidirectional → 128 features (64 forward + 64 backward)\")\n",
    "\n",
    "bi_model.summary()"
   ]
  }
