    "## 2. Stacked RNNs\n",
    "\n",
    "### Deep RNN Architecture\n",
    "\n",
    "**Single Layer RNN:**\n",
    "- Limited representation capacity\n",
    "- May not capture complex patterns\n",
    "\n",
    "**Stacked (Deep) RNN:**\n",
    "- Multiple RNN layers\n",
    "- Each layer learns different abstraction level\n",
    "- Layer 1: Low-level patterns\n",
    "- Layer 2: Mid-level patterns\n",
    "- Layer 3: High-level patterns\n",
    "\n",
    "### Implementation Tips\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **return_sequences=True**: Required for all layers except last\n",
    "2. **Dropout between layers**: Prevent overfitting\n",
    "3. **Decreasing units**: Common pattern (128 → 64 → 32)\n",
    "4. **2-3 layers**: Usually sufficient, more can overfit"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def create_stacked_lstm(vocab_size=10000, embedding_dim=128, \n",
    "                       max_length=100, num_classes=2):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Create stacked LSTM model\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Args:\n",
    "        vocab_size: Vocabulary size\n",
    "        embedding_dim: Embedding dimension\n",
    "        max_length: Maximum sequence length\n",
    "        num_classes: Number of output classes\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "        Stacked LSTM model\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    inputs = keras.Input(shape=(max_length,))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    x = layers.Embedding(vocab_size, embedding_dim)(inputs)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Layer 1: return_sequences=True to pass to next layer\n",
    "    x = layers.LSTM(128, return_sequences=True, dropout=0.2)(x)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Layer 2: return_sequences=True\n",
    "    x = layers.LSTM(64, return_sequences=True, dropout=0.2)(x)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Layer 3: return_sequences=False (default) for final output\n",
    "    x = layers.LSTM(32, dropout=0.2)(x)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Classification head\n",
    "    x = layers.Dense(64, activation='relu')(x)\n",
    "    x = layers.Dropout(0.5)(x)\n",
    "    outputs = layers.Dense(num_classes, activation='softmax')(x)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    model = Model(inputs, outputs, name='Stacked_LSTM')\n",
    "    return model\n",
    "\n",
    "stacked_model = create_stacked_lstm()\n",
    "print(\"Stacked LSTM model created\")\n",
    "print(\"\\nArchitecture: 3 LSTM layers with decreasing units (128 → 64 → 32)\")\n",
    "stacked_model.summary()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. GRU vs LSTM: Deep Comparison\n",
    "\n",
    "### LSTM (Long Short-Term Memory)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Gates:**\n",
    "- Forget gate: $f_t = \\sigma(W_f \\cdot [h_{t-1}, x_t] + b_f)$\n",
    "- Input gate: $i_t = \\sigma(W_i \\cdot [h_{t-1}, x_t] + b_i)$\n",
    "- Output gate: $o_t = \\sigma(W_o \\cdot [h_{t-1}, x_t] + b_o)$\n",
    "- Cell state: $C_t = f_t \\odot C_{t-1} + i_t \\odot \\tilde{C_t}$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Parameters:** 4 × (hidden_size × (hidden_size + input_size) + hidden_size)\n",
    "\n",
    "### GRU (Gated Recurrent Unit)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Gates:**\n",
    "- Reset gate: $r_t = \\sigma(W_r \\cdot [h_{t-1}, x_t] + b_r)$\n",
    "- Update gate: $z_t = \\sigma(W_z \\cdot [h_{t-1}, x_t] + b_z)$\n",
    "- Hidden state: $h_t = (1 - z_t) \\odot h_{t-1} + z_t \\odot \\tilde{h_t}$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Parameters:** 3 × (hidden_size × (hidden_size + input_size) + hidden_size)\n",
    "\n",
    "### Comparison Table\n",
    "\n",
    "| Feature | LSTM | GRU |\n",
    "|---------|------|-----|\n",
    "| **Gates** | 3 (forget, input, output) | 2 (reset, update) |\n",
    "| **Parameters** | More (~33% more) | Fewer |\n",
    "| **Training Speed** | Slower | Faster |\n",
    "| **Memory** | Separate cell state | Combined with hidden |\n",
    "| **Performance** | Better on complex tasks | Similar on simple tasks |\n",
    "| **Use Case** | Long sequences, complex | Short sequences, speed |\n",
    "\n",
    "### When to Choose\n",
    "\n",
    "**Choose LSTM:**\n",
    "- Very long sequences (>100 timesteps)\n",
    "- Complex temporal dependencies\n",
    "- When accuracy is critical\n",
    "- Sufficient computational resources\n",
    "\n",
    "**Choose GRU:**\n",
    "- Shorter sequences (<100 timesteps)\n",
    "- Limited computational resources\n",
    "- Faster training needed\n",
    "- Similar performance to LSTM observed"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def compare_lstm_gru():\n",
    "    \"\"\"Compare LSTM and GRU architectures\"\"\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # LSTM model\n",
    "    lstm_input = keras.Input(shape=(100,))\n",
    "    lstm_x = layers.Embedding(10000, 128)(lstm_input)\n",
    "    lstm_x = layers.LSTM(64)(lstm_x)\n",
    "    lstm_model = Model(lstm_input, lstm_x)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # GRU model\n",
    "    gru_input = keras.Input(shape=(100,))\n",
    "    gru_x = layers.Embedding(10000, 128)(gru_input)\n",
    "    gru_x = layers.GRU(64)(gru_x)\n",
    "    gru_model = Model(gru_input, gru_x)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(\"LSTM vs GRU Comparison:\")\n",
    "    print(\"=\" * 60)\n",
    "    print(f\"LSTM parameters: {lstm_model.count_params():,}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"GRU parameters: {gru_model.count_params():,}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    param_diff = (lstm_model.count_params() - gru_model.count_params()) / gru_model.count_params() * 100\n",
    "    print(f\"\\nLSTM has {param_diff:.1f}% more parameters than GRU\")\n",
    "    print(\"\\nRule of thumb: Start with GRU, switch to LSTM if needed\")\n",
    "    print(\"=\" * 60)\n",
    "\n",
    "compare_lstm_gru()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
